== Crispy Chips ==

Preheat the #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

== Burgers ==

Add the @BBQ sauce{1%sachet}, @breadcrumbs{1%pack} and @water{2%tbsp} (double for 4p) to a large #bowl{}.

Season with @salt{½%tsp} and @pepper{to taste} (double for 4p), then add the @Irish beef mince{250%g}.

Mix with your hands until well combined.

Roll the mince into evenly-sized balls, then flatten and shape into 2cm thick burgers (1 per person).

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the burgers until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-14%minutes}. Carefully turn every 3-4 mins and lower heat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: Burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When almost done, place @grated cheese{100%g} on top of each burger and cover pan to allow the cheese to melt, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once cooked, transfer the burgers from the pan and cover to keep warm.

== Honey Bacon ==

Give the pan a wipe then return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Lay in the @Irish bacon{170%g} and fry until crispy and brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side.

Add the @honey{1%sachet} and turn to coat.

Remove the pan from the heat and set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Cook bacon thoroughly.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop the sachet in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

== Tomato Salad ==

Meanwhile, halve, peel and finely chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped).

Roughly chop the @tomatoes{2}.

Add the tomato, onion and @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet} to a large bowl.

Season with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{1%tsp} (double for 4p). Mix until combined, then set aside.

== Assembly ==

A few mins before the chips are done, pop the @brioche buns{2} into the oven to warm, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything is ready, spread @aioli{1%sachet} over the cut side of each bun.

Lay a cheesy burger patty onto the bun base and top with the honeyed bacon.

Close the burger with the bun lid.

Serve with chips and salad alongside.